        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:30PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 229 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Aiken State Park, or 13 miles east of Aiken Mall,
moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Aiken State Park, Wagener, Springfield, Salley, Perry, Windsor, Aiken
Gopher Tortoise Heritage Preserve, and Perry Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
